						               													<description>Steinmannli consists of 4 different game variants&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. Solitaire&amp;#10;One player builds a tower of stones as high as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. Contest&amp;#10;2 to 4 players receive an equal amount of stones and build one tower by adding one stone after the other on a socle. Stones tumbling down must be collected by the player who caused the tumbling. The first player to get rid of all stones wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. Clean up&amp;#10;All stones are placed on a wooden board that is placed on a socle. 2 to 4 players remove the stones one by one until the board tumbles down or the last stone has been collected. The player with tho most stones collected wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4. Seesaw&amp;#10;A small wooden board is placed on a socle. 2 players receive an equal amount of stones and place them one by one on the small board. The player who makes the board tumble down, loses the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
